Add a `sidebarActiveTab` state field and `setSidebarActiveTab` action to the Zustand app store, with localStorage persistence.

## Interface Addition

In `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/app-store.ts`, add to the `AppState` interface:

```typescript
interface AppState {
  // ... existing fields ...

  sidebarActiveTab: 'sessions' | 'schedules' | 'connections';
  setSidebarActiveTab: (tab: 'sessions' | 'schedules' | 'connections') => void;
}
```

## Implementation

Add to the store implementation inside the `devtools(set => ({...}))` block, placed after the `sidebarOpen` / `setSidebarOpen` / `toggleSidebar` group for logical grouping:

```typescript
sidebarActiveTab: (() => {
  try {
    const stored = localStorage.getItem('dorkos-sidebar-active-tab');
    if (stored === 'sessions' || stored === 'schedules' || stored === 'connections') return stored;
  } catch {}
  return 'sessions';
})() as 'sessions' | 'schedules' | 'connections',
setSidebarActiveTab: (tab) => {
  try { localStorage.setItem('dorkos-sidebar-active-tab', tab); } catch {}
  set({ sidebarActiveTab: tab });
},
```

Note: This does NOT use the `readBool`/`writeBool` helpers because the value is a string union, not a boolean. The self-contained IIFE with try/catch follows the same pattern as `fontSize` and `fontFamily` in the existing store.

## resetPreferences Update

In the `resetPreferences` action, add cleanup for the new localStorage key. Add this line inside the `try` block alongside the other `localStorage.removeItem` calls:

```typescript
resetPreferences: () => {
  try {
    for (const lsKey of Object.values(BOOL_KEYS)) {
      localStorage.removeItem(lsKey);
    }
    localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEYS.FONT_SIZE);
    localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEYS.FONT_FAMILY);
    localStorage.removeItem('dorkos-sidebar-active-tab'); // ADD THIS LINE
  } catch {}
  // ... rest of reset ...
  set({
    ...BOOL_DEFAULTS,
    devtoolsOpen: false,
    fontSize: 'medium',
    fontFamily: DEFAULT_FONT,
    sidebarActiveTab: 'sessions', // ADD THIS LINE
  });
},
```

## Barrel Export

No changes needed to `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/index.ts` — `useAppStore` is already exported and consumers access `sidebarActiveTab` and `setSidebarActiveTab` through the store selector.

## Acceptance Criteria

- `useAppStore((s) => s.sidebarActiveTab)` returns `'sessions'` by default
- `useAppStore((s) => s.setSidebarActiveTab)('schedules')` updates state AND writes to `localStorage` key `'dorkos-sidebar-active-tab'`
- On page reload, the stored tab value is restored from localStorage
- `resetPreferences()` clears the localStorage key and resets state to `'sessions'`
- `pnpm typecheck` passes
- Existing `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/__tests__/app-store.test.ts` still passes

Create the `SidebarTabRow` component — a horizontal row of three icon buttons with ARIA tablist semantics and a motion-animated sliding indicator.

## File Location

`apps/client/src/layers/features/session-list/ui/SidebarTabRow.tsx`

## Props Interface

```typescript
import type { ReactNode } from 'react';

type SidebarTab = 'sessions' | 'schedules' | 'connections';

interface SidebarTabRowProps {
  activeTab: SidebarTab;
  onTabChange: (tab: SidebarTab) => void;
  schedulesBadge: number;
  connectionsStatus: 'ok' | 'partial' | 'error' | 'none';
  visibleTabs: SidebarTab[];
}
```

## Tab Definitions

```typescript
import { MessageSquare, Clock, Plug2 } from 'lucide-react';

const TAB_CONFIG = [
  { id: 'sessions' as const, icon: MessageSquare, label: 'Sessions', shortcut: '1' },
  { id: 'schedules' as const, icon: Clock, label: 'Schedules', shortcut: '2' },
  { id: 'connections' as const, icon: Plug2, label: 'Connections', shortcut: '3' },
] as const;
```

## Full Component Implementation

```tsx
import { useRef, useCallback } from 'react';
import { motion } from 'motion/react';
import { MessageSquare, Clock, Plug2 } from 'lucide-react';
import { cn } from '@/layers/shared/lib';
import { Tooltip, TooltipTrigger, TooltipContent } from '@/layers/shared/ui';

type SidebarTab = 'sessions' | 'schedules' | 'connections';

interface SidebarTabRowProps {
  activeTab: SidebarTab;
  onTabChange: (tab: SidebarTab) => void;
  schedulesBadge: number;
  connectionsStatus: 'ok' | 'partial' | 'error' | 'none';
  visibleTabs: SidebarTab[];
}

const TAB_CONFIG = [
  { id: 'sessions' as const, icon: MessageSquare, label: 'Sessions' },
  { id: 'schedules' as const, icon: Clock, label: 'Schedules' },
  { id: 'connections' as const, icon: Plug2, label: 'Connections' },
] as const;

const STATUS_DOT_COLORS: Record<string, string> = {
  ok: 'bg-green-500',
  partial: 'bg-amber-500',
  error: 'bg-red-500',
};

export function SidebarTabRow({
  activeTab,
  onTabChange,
  schedulesBadge,
  connectionsStatus,
  visibleTabs,
}: SidebarTabRowProps) {
  const tabListRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

  const handleKeyDown = useCallback(
    (e: React.KeyboardEvent) => {
      const currentIndex = visibleTabs.indexOf(activeTab);
      let nextIndex = currentIndex;

      if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') {
        nextIndex = (currentIndex + 1) % visibleTabs.length;
        e.preventDefault();
      } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') {
        nextIndex = (currentIndex - 1 + visibleTabs.length) % visibleTabs.length;
        e.preventDefault();
      }

      if (nextIndex !== currentIndex) {
        onTabChange(visibleTabs[nextIndex]);
        // Focus the newly active tab button
        const buttons = tabListRef.current?.querySelectorAll('[role="tab"]');
        (buttons?.[nextIndex] as HTMLElement)?.focus();
      }
    },
    [activeTab, onTabChange, visibleTabs]
  );

  const tabs = TAB_CONFIG.filter((t) => visibleTabs.includes(t.id));

  return (
    <div
      ref={tabListRef}
      role="tablist"
      aria-label="Sidebar views"
      className="border-border relative flex items-center gap-1 border-b px-2 py-1.5"
      onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
    >
      {tabs.map((tab, index) => {
        const isActive = activeTab === tab.id;
        const Icon = tab.icon;
        // Dynamic shortcut number based on visible position
        const shortcutNum = index + 1;

        return (
          <Tooltip key={tab.id}>
            <TooltipTrigger asChild>
              <button
                role="tab"
                id={`sidebar-tab-${tab.id}`}
                aria-selected={isActive}
                aria-controls={`sidebar-tabpanel-${tab.id}`}
                tabIndex={isActive ? 0 : -1}
                onClick={() => onTabChange(tab.id)}
                className={cn(
                  'relative rounded-md p-2 transition-colors duration-150',
                  isActive
                    ? 'text-foreground'
                    : 'text-muted-foreground/50 hover:text-muted-foreground'
                )}
              >
                <Icon className="size-(--size-icon-sm)" />

                {/* Schedules numeric badge */}
                {tab.id === 'schedules' && schedulesBadge > 0 && (
                  <span className="absolute -right-0.5 -top-0.5 flex size-4 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-green-500 text-[10px] font-medium text-white">
                    {schedulesBadge > 9 ? '9+' : schedulesBadge}
                    <span className="absolute inset-0 animate-pulse rounded-full bg-green-500/30" />
                  </span>
                )}

                {/* Connections status dot */}
                {tab.id === 'connections' && connectionsStatus !== 'none' && (
                  <span
                    className={cn(
                      'absolute -right-0.5 -top-0.5 size-1.5 rounded-full',
                      STATUS_DOT_COLORS[connectionsStatus]
                    )}
                  />
                )}

                {/* Sliding indicator */}
                {isActive && (
                  <motion.div
                    layoutId="sidebar-tab-indicator"
                    className="bg-foreground absolute right-0 bottom-[-7px] left-0 h-0.5 rounded-full"
                    transition={{ type: 'spring', stiffness: 280, damping: 32 }}
                  />
                )}
              </button>
            </TooltipTrigger>
            <TooltipContent side="bottom">
              {tab.label} {`\u2318${shortcutNum}`}
            </TooltipContent>
          </Tooltip>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Barrel Export

No barrel export needed — `SidebarTabRow` is only imported by `AgentSidebar.tsx` within the same feature module. Do NOT add it to `features/session-list/index.ts`.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Renders three tab buttons with `MessageSquare`, `Clock`, `Plug2` icons
- Active tab has `aria-selected="true"`, others have `aria-selected="false"`
- Each tab has `role="tab"`, container has `role="tablist"` with `aria-label="Sidebar views"`
- `aria-controls` links to corresponding `sidebar-tabpanel-{name}` IDs
- Arrow key navigation cycles focus between visible tabs
- Only visible tabs are rendered (filtering by `visibleTabs` prop)
- Schedules badge shows numeric count when `schedulesBadge > 0`, with pulsing ring animation
- Connections status dot renders with correct color (`bg-green-500` for ok, `bg-amber-500` for partial, `bg-red-500` for error, hidden for none)
- Sliding indicator uses `motion.div` with `layoutId="sidebar-tab-indicator"` and spring physics
- Tooltips show tab name and keyboard shortcut (e.g., "Sessions \u23181")
- `pnpm typecheck` passes

