## Status Derivation Logic

| Condition | Result |
|---|---|
| No adapters AND no agents | `'none'` |
| Any adapter has `status === 'error'` | `'error'` |
| All adapters connected AND all agents online | `'ok'` |
| Some adapters not connected OR some agents offline | `'partial'` |

## Important Notes

- This hook imports from `entities/agent`, `entities/relay`, and `entities/mesh` — this is FSD-compliant (features can import from entities)
- The hook reuses the same TanStack Query caches as other components — no additional API calls
- `useRelayAdapters` returns `AdapterListItem[]` where each item has a `status` field (string: 'connected', 'idle', 'error')
- `useRegisteredAgents` returns `{ agents: Agent[] }` where each agent has a `status` field (string: 'online', 'offline')
- The hook does NOT create new polling — it piggybacks on existing query caches from `useRelayAdapters` (10s poll) and `useRegisteredAgents` (30s stale time)

## Acceptance Criteria

- Returns `'none'` when no adapters or agents exist (both arrays empty)
- Returns `'ok'` when all adapters have `status === 'connected'` and all agents have `status === 'online'`
- Returns `'partial'` when some adapters are idle or some agents are offline
- Returns `'error'` when any adapter has `status === 'error'`
- Returns `'none'` when features are disabled (queries return undefined)
- Connections tab badge dot in `SidebarTabRow` reflects the computed status
- `pnpm typecheck` passes

